# Accessibility Standards

## Interaction and Navigation
- Use `<button>` for actions and `<a>` for navigation.
- Never use clickable `div`/`span` unless it includes `role="button"` and `tabIndex={0}`.
- Never remove focus outlines without a strong `:focus-visible` style.
- Interactive controls should have a minimum 44x44px target area.

## Text and Content
- Keep heading hierarchy logical; one `h1` per page.
- Every `<img>` needs `alt`; decorative images use `alt=""`.
- Icon-only buttons must include an `aria-label`.

## Forms
- Each field needs a `<label>` or `aria-labelledby`.
- Invalid fields must use `aria-invalid="true"` and connect errors via `aria-describedby`.

## Structure
- Use landmarks: `<header>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<footer>`, `<article>`, `<section>`.
- Use proper lists (`<ul>`/`<ol>` with `<li>`).
